narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
Strength: we talked about interesting problems in analysis, pretty challenging ones.
Weakness: Lectures were not the most organized, and I felt material was not covered thoroughly enough prior to tackling those problems.

Strengths - for the little material that was covered, it was covered quite well. The final project problem is very flexible.

Weaknesses - there wasn't much material.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Definitely. Peter Jones is the best professor at Yale I have encountered. He loves teaching and encouraged me to tackle hard problems.
It's not a classic rigorous math class. You will learn some new things but most of the time it will feel a little confusing and a bit hand-wavy.

Yes. If you make the time to meet with Professor Jones outside of class, it helps solidify your understanding and makes the class more enjoyable. He's a really great professor and you can learn a lot by meeting with him outside of class.
Yes. you can learn mathematical knowledge for further study.
